  "prompt": "How do we forget any Wi-Fi in Windows 10?",
  "response": "To forget a Wi-Fi network in Windows 10, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Settings**:\n   - Click on the **Start menu** (Windows icon) at the bottom left corner of your screen.\n   - Select the **Settings** icon (gear icon).\n\n2. **Network & Internet**:\n   - In the Settings window, click on **Network & Internet**.\n\n3. **Wi-Fi**:\n   - On the left sidebar, click on **Wi-Fi**.\n\n4. **Manage Known Networks**:\n   - Scroll down and click on **Manage known networks**.\n\n5. **Forget the Network**:\n   - You will see a list of all the Wi-Fi networks you have connected to. Find the network you want to forget.\n   - Click on the network name, and then click on the **Forget** button that appears.\n\nAfter following these steps, your Windows 10 device will no longer remember the selected Wi-Fi network, and you will need to enter the password again if you choose to connect to it in the future.",
